body.description: Improve your gum health up to 100% better than a manual toothbrush with the ProtectiveClean 5100 rechargeable electric toothbrush. It has a pressure sensor that protects teeth and gums from excess brushing pressure. Brush heads wear out over time. Our BrushSync technology tracks how long you have been using your Optimal Gum Care brush head and how hard you have been brushing. Your electric toothbrush will beep to inform you when to replace your brush head. Customize your own brushing experience with your choice of 3 modes: Clean, White and Gum Care. The easy-start feature slowly increases the power of the brush as you get used to the Sonicare experience and the SmarTimer encourages a full 2 minutes brushing time as recommended by your dental professional. The battery charge indicator light lets you know when it is time recharge; 2 week battery life. The kit includes 1 Black ProtectiveClean 5100 handle, 1 Optimal Gum Care brush head, 1 black charger, 1 black travel case. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I finally got my Electric Toothbrush!
reviews.reviewText: From the moment I switched to the Philips Sonicare Protective Clean 5100 Gum Health, my dental care routine transformed into a refreshing experience. This electric power toothbrush is a game-changer for anyone serious about maintaining their oral health.Design & Build Quality:The sleek and ergonomic design of this toothbrush feels great in hand. The premium build quality exudes durability and reassurance. The brush handle offers a secure grip, ensuring easy maneuverability while brushing.Gum Health Mode:The Gum Health mode is an absolute winner. This feature is a lifesaver for those like me who are prone to gum issues. It provides a gentle but effective clean, leaving your gums feeling revitalized and healthier after every use. No more bleeding or irritation—just pure gum health.Cleaning Performance:The sonic technology is the real star here. It pulses and vibrates to create a dynamic cleaning action that removes up to 7x more plaque compared to manual brushing. The bristles are gentle on teeth yet powerful in their cleaning abilities. I could feel the difference after my very first use.Smart Pressure Sensor:One of my favorite aspects of the Protective Clean 5100 is the smart pressure sensor. It ensures that I don't brush too hard, protecting my teeth and gums from unnecessary damage. The handle gently vibrates to alert you when you're applying too much pressure. It's a simple but highly effective feature.Battery Life:The long-lasting battery life is impressive. I can go weeks without needing to recharge, making it an ideal travel companion. The charger is easy to use and doesn't take up much space.Ease of Use:This toothbrush is incredibly user-friendly. Just press a button, and it does all the work for you. It has a built-in timer that encourages you to brush for the recommended two minutes, ensuring a thorough clean every time.App Compatibility:For those who love to track their brushing habits, the Philips Sonicare app is a helpful addition. It provides real-time feedback and personalized guidance to improve your brushing routine. Syncing the brush to the app is straightforward and enhances your overall oral care experience.In conclusion, the Philips Sonicare Protective Clean 5100 Gum Health, Rechargeable Electric Power Toothbrush is more than just a toothbrush; it's a complete dental care system. It has revolutionized the way I care for my teeth and gums. My dental checkups have never been better, and my dentist is impressed with the positive changes in my oral health.If you're seeking a top-notch electric toothbrush that not only cleans but pampers your gums and ensures long-term oral health, look no further. The Protective Clean 5100 is the answer. It's an investment in your smile, and one that you won't regret. Say goodbye to oral care woes and hello to a healthier, happier mouth with this fantastic toothbrush.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 21, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great toothbrush and horrible customer service
reviews.reviewText: This toothbrush is really great because it has 3 modes. Clean, whiten, and gum care. I have owned sonicare toothbrushes for about the last 30 year's. I'm having a problem with this brush but it is all due to sonicare customer service. The people working there don't know what they're doing and they put me on hold constantly. My amber light on my brush came on and the first representative I talked to told me I needed a new charger. I looked up the information in the manual and saw that this means I need new toothbrush heads. I don't think I have had the brush that long to need new heads already. My other brushes were not like this. Well good luck getting a representative to tell you which brush head is correct for your brush. Every person told me a different thing. Also, they wanted the serial number on the bottom of my brush which I can't read because I am 65 years old and cannot see this number. I have my model number. Anyway, eventually I was told I need toothbrush head HX 9062. I put this on my Amazon wishlist to save it since I was given so many different toothbrush head numbers. They mailed me a diamond head brush head. It's the wrong head but they said it doesn't matter as they all snap on. I am so disappointed in Sonicare. I remember buying toothbrushes from them and when they stopped working they mailed you a new one. This customer service now is horrible. They have absolutely no customer service. My son just got a job with Phillips recently working in a laboratory building ultrasound machines. I told him about my problems and he said sonicare is outsourced. That is obvious by their lack of knowledge and customer service. This is additional information since my original post. Today I received 3 packages from FedEx with toothbrush heads. Two of the heads are correct and one is incorrect. I will save myself from all this stress by ordering from Amazon

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good brush, but long term quality issue
reviews.reviewText: Bought 2nd one as a replacement, Philip's customer service is usually great. Battery lasts great, even after 3+ years of use. Both toothbrushes had the same issue, the vibrating tip comes loose after a year or two. You'll notice the tip is wobbly and the brush sounds louder. Reason for that is that the tip is fastened with a simple metal screw which when vibrating over time tends to get loose or in my case entirely undone. There's a video on how to fix it relatively easily, but I wish it would not come loose at all.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I really like this electric toothbrush. My teeth feel very clean after using it. I find it really easy to replace the brush head- not difficult to pull off or put a new one on. I love that this toothbrush has a light come on to remind when to replace a new one. I bought the replacement heads here on Amazon as well for like a pack of 12 or so. Not a bad price either. Lastly, I went on a weekend trip and didn’t pack the charger. The charge held up for the weekend as well. I also liked the added bonus of having a case for this toothbrush. Overall, this is better than my last electric toothbrush and has held up so far.
